You mean, the same way that Bandai Entertainment and Viz was
absorbed into Pioneer/Geneon when Pioneer/Geneon handled the
distribution of *their* titles?

This seems to be a distribution deal, nothing more.  It has
happened many times before, with varying players.  Pioneer
handled distribution for others, earlier.  ADV did and does for
some others.  I believe CPM handled distribution for some other
companies for a while too.

Buena Vista/Disney handles distribution for Studio Ghibli in
Japan.  Ghibli hasn't merged into Disney yet...

Outsorcing distribution is *very* common, in all types of
business, not just video.

If you want to convince us that Geneon USA will fold or be bought
out, you need to show some better evidence than a distribution
deal.

